<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANCER CENTER GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The W. M. Keck Foundation has awarded a $1.8-million grant to the cancer center 
at St. John's Hospital and Health Center in Santa Monica. Hospital officials 
said it was the largest single donation that the hospital has received. 
</P>
<P>
The cancer center is a comprehensive facility devoted to the early detection, 
treatment and prevention of cancer. It offers a variety of inpatient and 
outpatient services and educational programs. 
</P>
<P>
The Keck Foundation, based in Los Angeles, was established by William M. Keck, 
the late founder of Superior Oil Co. A major contributor to colleges and 
universities throughout the country, the foundation also provides support for 
education, health care, community service and arts programs in Southern 
California. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
